A 'sparklyr' extension adding the capability to work easily with nested data.

name: r-sparklyr.nested
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.0.4' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sparklyr.nested
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/sparklyr.nested_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/sparklyr.nested/sparklyr.nested_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ecece96001c8c2acbe9dae2b68ac2dd166be038d2e92f06ce6cfa19200c1aca0

build:
  number: 2
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/
  missing_dso_whitelist:
    - '*/R.dll'        # [win]
    - '*/Rblas.dll'    # [win]
    - '*/Rlapack.dll'  # [win]

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-listviewer
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-sparklyr
    - r-tidyselect
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-listviewer
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-sparklyr
    - r-tidyselect

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sparklyr.nested')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sparklyr.nested')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=sparklyr.nested
  license: Apache-2.0
  summary: A 'sparklyr' extension adding the capability to work easily with nested data.
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file:
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
